# Responsive mobile-first development

## Workflow

- Start layout decisions at **narrow widths** first, then scale up
- Sections should remain **readable, tappable, and balanced** between standard breakpoints
- Avoid layouts that only work at a single exact width

## Widths to sanity-check

| Width | Role |
|-------|------|
| 320–430px | Phones |
| 768px | Tablet |
| 1024px | Laptop |
| 1280px+ | Desktop |

## Expectations

- No horizontal overflow from fixed widths; use `max-w-*`, fluid grids, and sensible image sizing
- Touch targets for primary actions remain usable on small screens
- Do not rely on **hover-only** affordances for essential content
- Full-height sections (`min-h-[100dvh]`, etc.) should still allow scrolling and visibility of key CTAs on short viewports
